  "text": "In the cold pressor test the right hand was completely immersed in ice water (0°C to 4°C) for 1 minute. During the mental arithmetic test, the subjects were asked to subtract the number \"13\" repetitively starting from \"1079\" for 5 minutes while a metronome made noise at a frequency of 2 Hz. They were informed about any miscalculation. After each test there was a 30-minute recovery period. Arterial blood for catecholamine assay was collected after 30 minutes of supine rest, after 30 seconds and 1 minute of the cold pressor test, and after 1, 3, and 5 minutes of the mental arithmetic test. Catecholamine responses to stress tests were calculated as the mean value during stress subtracting the baseline value before the test. Blood was drawn in 10-mL glass tubes containing glutathione and EGTA, and plasma catecholamines were measured by radioenzymatic technique according to Peuler and Johnson, 23 as reported previously. [CITATION_1] 24 All of the samples were analyzed by the same blinded technician.",
